Sentence: Samples 2 and 3 respec- tively had onset transition temperatures of 38.9 K and 39.6 K with sharp transition widths of about 0.8 K and 0.6 K, com- parable with those of high-quality planar MgB 2 films fabri- cated on single crystal substrates by HPCVD.
The binary intermetallic compound MgB 2 has attracted great interest in both fundamental studies and practical applications since its superconductivity was discovered in 2001 .
MgB 2 films 10 Î¼m thick have been fabricated on the outer surface of a polycrystalline Al 2 O 3 cylinder.

Due to its remarkable superconducting properties, such as high superconducting transition temperature (T C ) of 39 K [2], simple crystalline structure, high critical current density (J C ) [3], and absence of weak links at grain boundaries [4], MgB 2 is considered to be one of the most promising super- conducting materials for such applications as medium- strength superconducting magnets , Josephson junction devices , and digital circuits .
